        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer283319202" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13986403301517520608">Mudan Ting is arguably the &quot;classic&quot; of Chinese drama, with a complex storyline and characterization that spans Daoism, Biddhism, Confucianism and in the end a plain old love story. An additional joy of this edition is that Cyril Birch is that rare talent who is both a translator and a good writer in English. In particular, his english prose versions of the Chinese song couplets work well. Where other translations of Chinese classics can stumble over some pretty rough rocks when in the poetic se</span>
  <span id="freeText13986403301517520608" style="display:none">Mudan Ting is arguably the "classic" of Chinese drama, with a complex storyline and characterization that spans Daoism, Biddhism, Confucianism and in the end a plain old love story. An additional joy of this edition is that Cyril Birch is that rare talent who is both a translator and a good writer in English. In particular, his english prose versions of the Chinese song couplets work well. Where other translations of Chinese classics can stumble over some pretty rough rocks when in the poetic sections- Birch guides the ship to a happy destination.<br /><br />I took off one star only because I would have loved further documentation on the chorus melodies</span>
  <a data-text-id="13986403301517520608" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
